## Modules[§](https://docs.rs/httptest/latest/httptest/#modules)

[matchers](https://docs.rs/httptest/latest/httptest/matchers/index.html "mod httptest::matchers")
    Matcher implementations.

[responders](https://docs.rs/httptest/latest/httptest/responders/index.html "mod httptest::responders")
    Responder implementations.
## Macros[§](https://docs.rs/httptest/latest/httptest/#macros)

[all_of](https://docs.rs/httptest/latest/httptest/macro.all_of.html "macro httptest::all_of")
    true if all the provided matchers return true.

[any_of](https://docs.rs/httptest/latest/httptest/macro.any_of.html "macro httptest::any_of")
    true if any of the provided matchers return true.

[cycle](https://docs.rs/httptest/latest/httptest/macro.cycle.html "macro httptest::cycle")
    a Responder that cycles through a list of responses.
## Structs[§](https://docs.rs/httptest/latest/httptest/#structs)

[Expectation](https://docs.rs/httptest/latest/httptest/struct.Expectation.html "struct httptest::Expectation")
    An expectation to be asserted by the server.

[ExpectationBuilder](https://docs.rs/httptest/latest/httptest/struct.ExpectationBuilder.html "struct httptest::ExpectationBuilder")
    Define expectations using a builder pattern.

[Server](https://docs.rs/httptest/latest/httptest/struct.Server.html "struct httptest::Server")
    The Server

[ServerBuilder](https://docs.rs/httptest/latest/httptest/struct.ServerBuilder.html "struct httptest::ServerBuilder")
    Custom Server Builder.

[ServerHandle](https://docs.rs/httptest/latest/httptest/struct.ServerHandle.html "struct httptest::ServerHandle")
    A handle to a server. Expectations are inserted when the handle is dropped.

[ServerPool](https://docs.rs/httptest/latest/httptest/struct.ServerPool.html "struct httptest::ServerPool")
    A pool of shared servers.
## Traits[§](https://docs.rs/httptest/latest/httptest/#traits)

[IntoTimes](https://docs.rs/httptest/latest/httptest/trait.IntoTimes.html "trait httptest::IntoTimes")
    How many times is an expectation expected to occur. Implemented for usize and any range of usize values.

